 quiet about this.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Silent. All sessions match baseline — no new failures, no blockers, no state transitions since 15:30 UTC.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1181,\n            \"output\": 341,\n            \"totalTokens\": 24031,\n            \"cacheRead\": 14264,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 8245,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776182455699,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d97b85016ae1495c17ff68809daf5\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"b986697a\",\n            \"seq\": 8\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776182139549,\n      \"sessionId\": \"ff900ac5-4016-44d5-9d31-471e538dc956\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 45207,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776182138683,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/ff900ac5-4016-44d5-9d31-471e538dc956.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I have a comprehensive view of all sessions. Let me analyze the active sessions (excluding this cron session):\\n\\n**Running sessions (excluding this cron e7885813):**\\n1. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — \\\"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\\\" — running — updatedAt 1776182062086\\n2. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — \\\"Cron: 5p Progress Report\\\" — running — updatedAt 1776181896936\\n\\n\\n3. `telegram:group:-5163901258` — \\\"QLHV group\\\" — running — updatedAt 1776178681406\\n\\nI'm also noticing some zombie sessions that are still marked as running but appear stuck. There's one cron job from 11:53 UTC that looks inactive, another cron that's stuck with an incomplete label about sending messages to a Telegram group, and a few subagent sessions that never properly initialized. I should focus on the ones that are actually responding.\\n\\nLooking at the timestamp conversions from 1776182139549ms, that's 15:55 UTC on April 14th. For the cron sessions, I'm calculating the duration from when they started to now—the first one has been running for about 8 minutes, the second for roughly 23 minutes, and the third is still being determined.\\n\\nFor the QLHV group, the runtime shows it ended after 8 seconds, but the updatedAt timestamp is much more recent at 15:38 UTC, suggesting it's been actively communicating despite the short runtime measurement.\\n\\nI'm noticing a discrepancy with cron:e7885813 — the previous status message was sent at 15:44 UTC, which is well within the 5-minute interval, so it should still be running. The main and DTLX group Telegram sessions are both done, and cron:b653a6c0 appears to be a zombie with no recent updates. I need to exclude the current cron session from the report and focus on the running sessions: the three cron sessions and the QLHV group. For the durations, I'm calculating from their start times—cron:e7885813 has been running for about 11 minutes since 15:44 UTC, and the others started earlier at 15:32 and 15:38 UTC respectively. I'm seeing that the previous report was sent at 15:44 UTC and I have a new cron trigger at 15:55 UTC