nd matching the baseline state. I notice cron:e7885813 actually sent a message to the Lead just a few minutes ago at 15:55 UTC, so that's a fresh heartbeat despite its older session ID. The important thing is there are no new failures, blockers, or critical status changes—everything's stable and healthy, so I should stay quiet about this."},{"type":"text","text":"Silent. All sessions match baseline — no new failures, no blockers, no state transitions since 15:30 UTC."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1181,"output":341,"totalTokens":24031,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":8245,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776182455699,"responseId":"062d97b85016ae1495c17ff68809daf5","__openclaw":{"id":"b986697a","seq":8}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","kind":"other","channel":"unknown","label":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","displayName":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","updatedAt":1776182139549,"sessionId":"ff900ac5-4016-44d5-9d31-471e538dc956","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45207,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776182138683,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/ff900ac5-4016-44d5-9d31-471e538dc956.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view of all sessions. Let me analyze the active sessions (excluding this cron session):\n\n**Running sessions (excluding this cron e7885813):**\n1. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" — running — updatedAt 1776182062086\n2. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" — running — updatedAt 1776181896936\n\n\n3. `telegram:group:-5163901258` — \"QLHV group\" — running — updatedAt 1776178681406\n\nI'm also noticing some zombie sessions that are still marked as running but appear stuck. There's one cron job from 11:53 UTC that looks inactive, another cron that's stuck with an incomplete label about sending messages to a Telegram group, and a few subagent sessions that never properly initialized. I should focus on the ones that are actually responding.\n\nLooking at the timestamp conversions from 1776182139549ms, that's 15:55 UTC on April 14th. For the cron sessions, I'm calculating the duration from when they started to now—the first one has been running for about 8 minutes, the second for roughly 23 minutes, and the third is still being determined.\n\nFor the QLHV group, the runtime shows it ended after 8 seconds, but the updatedAt timestamp is much more recent at 15:38 UTC, suggesting it's been actively communicating despite the short runtime measurement.\n\nI'm noticing a discrepancy with cron:e7885813 — the previous status message was sent at 15:44 UTC, which is well within the 5-minute interval, so it should still be running. The main and DTLX group Telegram sessions are both done, and cron:b653a6c0 appears to be a zombie with no recent updates. I need to exclude the current cron session from the report and focus on the running sessions: the three cron sessions and the QLHV group. For the durations, I'm calculating from their start times—cron:e7885813 has been running for about 11 minutes since 15:44 UTC, and the others started earlier at 15:32 and 15:38 UTC respectively. I'm seeing that the previous report was sent at 15:44 UTC and I have a new cron trigger at 15:55 UTC, so I should send an updated status report to the Lead. I'll include the zombie sessions in the report since they were noted as warnings before, though I need to verify the timeline for when they stopped running. The main session ended and the DTLX group session ended as well, so I've got three cron sessions and one QLHV group session currently running. Now I'm formatting this into a clean status report for the user, keeping the zombie sessions noted since they were flagged as warnings."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kvc1o5qv47mp_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 15:55 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~23m ago\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~24m ago\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status → Lead): running — 5-min heartbeat status to Lead — running now\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosystem session — ~17m ago\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: ⚠️ 2 zombie cron sessions lingering (cron:b653a6c0, cron:ac986a8d — pre-existing, no failures)\n• No new failures, no blockers.\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":28743,"output":904,"totalTokens":43786,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":290,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776182151140,"responseId":"062d9688a32afa2a292ae4ca6af21b89","__openclaw":{"id":"444338a1","seq":4}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Got a gateway timeout. Let me try again."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ntoth1xun0x4_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 15:55 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 4\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~23m ago\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~24m ago\n• cron:e7885813 (Agent Status → Lead): running — 5-min heartbeat status to Lead — running now\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosystem session — ~17m ago\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 